#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.28:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.28:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga "
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.28:0.3"
msgid "28. Lokasutta "
msgstr "28. The World "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn56.28:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ariyasaccāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four noble truths. "

msgctxt "sn56.28:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.28:1.3"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ. "
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.28:1.4"
msgid "Sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya tathāgato ariyo; "
msgstr "In this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans, the Realized One is the Noble One. "

msgctxt "sn56.28:1.5"
msgid "tasmā ‘ariyasaccānī’ti vuccanti. "
msgstr "That’s why they’re called ‘noble truths’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.28:2.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.28:2.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
